    featured: false,
    type: "grant-news",
    content: `
      <h2>The Colorado Tech Ecosystem in 2026</h2>
      <p>Colorado has firmly established itself as a top-tier technology hub, rivaling the coasts with a vibrant ecosystem centered around Denver, Boulder, and Colorado Springs. For 2026-2027, the state has doubled down on its commitment to advanced industries, offering a robust suite of grants and incentives designed to accelerate startup growth.</p>
      <p>The state's Office of Economic Development and International Trade (OEDIT) manages the primary funding vehicle: the <strong>Advanced Industries (AI) Accelerator Program</strong>. This program is critical for early-stage companies in aerospace, bioscience, electronics, energy, and information technology.</p>

      <h3>Key Funding Programs</h3>
      
      <h4>1. Advanced Industries (AI) Early-Stage Capital and Retention Grant</h4>
      <p>This is the flagship grant for Colorado startups. It provides non-dilutive capital to help companies commercialize innovative technologies.</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Funding Amount:</strong> Up to $250,000.</li>
        <li><strong>Purpose:</strong> Commercialization, product development, and manufacturing scale-up.</li>
        <li><strong>Match Requirement:</strong> 2:1 match (you must raise $2 for every $1 of grant funding).</li>
        <li><strong>Eligibility:</strong> Must be an "Advanced Industry" company with headquarters in Colorado.</li>
      </ul>

      <h4>2. Proof of Concept (POC) Grant</h4>
      <p>Designed for pre-revenue companies and researchers, this grant helps bridge the gap between initial research and market viability.</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Funding Amount:</strong> Up to $150,000.</li>
        <li><strong>Focus:</strong> Validating technology, building prototypes, and market testing.</li>
        <li><strong>Partnership:</strong> Often requires collaboration with a Colorado research university.</li>
      </ul>

      <h4>3. Advanced Industries Export Grant</h4>
      <p>For tech companies looking to go global, this grant reimburses international business development costs.</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Funding Amount:</strong> Up to $15,000.</li>
        <li><strong>Usage:</strong> Trade show exhibition fees, translation services, and legal fees for intellectual property protection abroad.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>The Clean Energy Opportunity</h2>
      <p>Colorado is aggressively pursuing 100% renewable energy goals. The <strong>Colorado Clean Energy Fund</strong> acts as a "Green Bank" to provide low-cost financing for clean tech deployment. Additionally, the state offers specific incentives for:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Geothermal Energy:</strong> New tax credits for geothermal drilling and equipment.</li>
        <li><strong>Electric Vehicles:</strong> Fleet conversion grants and charging infrastructure rebates.</li>
        <li><strong>Building Electrification:</strong> Incentives for heat pumps and energy efficiency upgrades in commercial buildings.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Tax Credits: The Hidden Capital</h2>
      <p>Grants are great, but tax credits can be just as valuable for extending your runway.</p>
      
      <h3>Job Growth Incentive Tax Credit</h3>
      <p>If your startup is creating jobs, you can receive a state income tax credit equal to 50% of the FICA paid by the employee.</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Requirement:</strong> Create at least 20 new jobs (or 5 in Enterprise Zones) with wages at least 110% of the county average.</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Advanced Industry Investment Tax Credit</h3>
      <p>This is a powerful tool for attracting investors. It provides a <strong>25-30% tax credit</strong> to investors who put money into your qualified Colorado small business. This effectively reduces the risk for your angel investors, making it easier for you to raise your seed round.</p>

      <h2>Application Strategy</h2>
      <p>Competition for the AI Accelerator grants is fierce. Successful applicants typically:</p>
      <ol>
        <li><strong>Demonstrate Local Impact:</strong> Clearly articulate how the grant will create high-paying jobs in Colorado.</li>
        <li><strong>Secure the Match:</strong> Have your matching funds (LOIs or bank statements) ready before you apply.</li>
        <li><strong>Engage Reviewers:</strong> Use the "draft review" period if offered. OEDIT staff feedback is invaluable.</li>
      </ol>

      <div class="bg-blue-50 p-6 rounded-lg my-8 border-l-4 border-blue-600">
        <h3 class="text-blue-800 font-bold text-lg mb-2">Need Help?</h3>
        <p class="text-blue-700">The <strong>Innosphere Ventures</strong> incubator in Fort Collins and <strong>Techstars</strong> in Boulder are key ecosystem partners. They often help portfolio companies navigate these state grant applications.</p>
      </div>
    `,
